  "seafarer-recruitment": "const faqs = [\n  { q:\"What is seafarer recruitment?\", a:\"Seafarer recruitment is the process of sourcing, screening, verifying, and placing qualified maritime professionals onboard vessels. It involves identifying candidates for specific ranks and vessel types, checking certifications and sea service records, conducting competency interviews, and coordinating documentation and embarkation logistics.\" },\n  { q:\"What does a seafarer recruitment agency do?\", a:\"A seafarer recruitment agency manages the complete crew sourcing process on behalf of shipowners and vessel operators — from candidate identification and STCW certificate verification through to interview support, documentation coordination, and deployment planning. ShipCrewAgency handles all stages so your marine HR team can focus on fleet operations.\" },\n  { q:\"Why should shipowners use a maritime recruitment agency?\", a:\"Using a specialist maritime recruitment agency provides faster hiring, lower compliance risk, access to a pre-verified candidate pool, and significant reduction in internal HR workload. A specialist agency understands maritime regulations, vessel-type requirements, and can respond efficiently for both planned and emergency crew needs.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you recruit both officers and ratings?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency recruits across all deck crew ranks including Masters, Chief Officers, Second Officers, Third Officers, Bosun, Able Seaman, Ordinary Seaman, and all engine and catering crew. We cover the full vessel complement.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you provide engine crew recruitment?\", a:\"Yes. We recruit all engineering positions including Chief Engineer, Second Engineer, Third Engineer, Fourth Engineer, Oiler, Motorman, and Wiper. All engine crew candidates are matched to your vessel's machinery type and maintenance requirements.\" },\n  { q:\"Are your seafarers STCW certified?\", a:\"Yes. STCW certification is verified for every candidate according to their rank, vessel type, and client requirements. This includes basic safety training, watchkeeping certificates, advanced firefighting, medical first aid, tanker endorsements, and any vessel-specific certifications required for the role.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you follow MLC 2006 recruitment standards?\", a:\"Yes. Our recruitment practices align with MLC 2006 standards, covering fair and transparent recruitment procedures, employment conditions, seafarer welfare, and maritime labour standards to protect both vessel operators and seafarers.\" },\n  { q:\"How long does seafarer recruitment take?\", a:\"Recruitment timelines depend on rank, vessel type, joining port, documentation requirements, visa processing time, and urgency level. Planned crew changes can be prepared well in advance. Emergency replacements can be actioned significantly faster using our pre-screened candidate database.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you provide emergency seafarer recruitment?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency provides urgent crew replacement support for illness, missed joining, failed documentation, visa delays, or sudden crew shortages. We maintain a ready database of pre-screened, compliant seafarers to respond quickly without compromising on certification or compliance standards.\" },\n  { q:\"What vessel types do you recruit for?\", a:\"We recruit for oil tankers, LPG carriers, LNG carriers, bulk carriers, container ships, general cargo vessels, offshore support vessels, tugboats, passenger ships, and heavy lift vessels. Each vessel type requires specific experience and certifications which we verify as part of our standard screening.\" },\n  { q:\"How do you verify candidate quality?\", a:\"Our verification process includes credential checks, STCW certificate review, sea service record confirmation, employer reference checks, competency interviews, background screening, and evaluation of relevant vessel-type experience. This multi-stage process ensures candidates meet both regulatory and operational requirements.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you help with crew documentation?\", a:\"Yes. We support the documentation process covering passports, seaman books, certificates, medical fitness documents, visas, flag-state endorsements, employment agreements, and joining logistics coordination.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you recruit seafarers for LNG and tanker vessels?\", a:\"Yes. We specialise in recruitment for tanker and gas carrier operations, including verification of tanker endorsements, gas carrier certification, cargo handling experience, and the specific safety training required for LNG and LPG vessels.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you offer temporary and permanent recruitment?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency supports both short-term temporary hiring for crew rotation gaps, sickness cover, and project voyages, as well as long-term permanent maritime recruitment for shipowners and ship management companies building a stable talent pipeline.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you support international crew deployment?\", a:\"Yes. We provide support with visa coordination, travel planning, port joining logistics, and embarkation documentation for international crew deployment across global trading routes.\" },\n  { q:\"What is the cost of seafarer recruitment?\", a:\"Recruitment costs vary depending on rank, contract duration, vessel type, urgency level, and the scope of deployment support required. Contact our team with your specific vessel requirements to receive a transparent recruitment proposal.\" },\n  { q:\"What happens if a selected seafarer becomes unavailable?\", a:\"If a confirmed seafarer becomes unavailable before joining, ShipCrewAgency provides replacement support and access to alternative pre-screened candidates from our database to minimise disruption to your vessel schedule.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you support crew retention?\", a:\"Yes. Our recruitment approach emphasises role-fit matching, candidate quality control, and post-placement performance feedback. This retention-focused methodology helps reduce early contract departures and supports longer seafarer tenure onboard.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you conduct interviews before placement?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency conducts internal candidate interviews as part of the screening process. We also coordinate and support client-side interviews where required, ensuring only suitable, well-assessed candidates are presented for your consideration.\" },\n  { q:\"How can we request a seafarer recruitment proposal?\", a:\"Contact ShipCrewAgency with your vessel type, required ranks, expected joining date, contract duration, flag state, and any specific compliance or operational requirements. Our recruitment team will review your needs and respond with a tailored crew supply proposal.\" }\n];\n\nfunction buildFAQs() {\n  const list = document.getElementById('faqList');\n  faqs.forEach(f => {\n    const item = document.createElement('div');\n    item.className = 'faq-item';\n    item.innerHTML = `\n      <button class=\"faq-btn\" onclick=\"toggleFAQ(this)\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n        <span>${f.q}</span>\n        <svg class=\"faq-ico\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\">\n          <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" d=\"M12 6v6m0 0v6m0-6h6m-6 0H6\"/>\n        </svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-body\">\n        <p class=\"faq-ans\">${f.a}</p>\n      </div>`;\n    list.appendChild(item);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction toggleFAQ(btn) {\n  const body = btn.nextElementSibling;\n  const isOpen = body.classList.contains('open');\n  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-body.open').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('open'));\n  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-btn.open').forEach(b => { b.classList.remove('open'); b.setAttribute('aria-expanded','false'); });\n  if (!isOpen) {\n    body.classList.add('open');\n    btn.classList.add('open');\n    btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded','true');\n  }\n}\n\nfunction submitForm() {\n  document.getElementById('recruitmentForm').style.display = 'none';\n  document.getElementById('formSuccess').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\nbuildFAQs();",
