  "offshore-manning": "const faqs = [\n  { q:\"What is offshore crew manning?\", a:\"Offshore crew manning is the sourcing, vetting, certification checking, deployment, and management of crew and technical personnel for offshore vessels, rigs, subsea projects, offshore wind, oil and gas operations, and marine construction. It covers everything from initial candidate identification through to crew rotation and ongoing workforce continuity.\" },\n  { q:\"How is offshore crew manning different from regular ship crew manning?\", a:\"Offshore crewing requires additional safety training, technical certifications, offshore medical fitness, rotation planning, project-specific readiness, and experience with high-risk offshore environments. Standard maritime crew may hold STCW certificates but lack the OPITO, BOSIET, HUET, offshore medical, and technical qualifications required for offshore operations.\" },\n  { q:\"What offshore vessel types do you support?\", a:\"We support OSVs, PSVs, AHTS vessels, drill ships, FPSO units, semi-submersible rigs, jack-up rigs, offshore construction vessels, subsea support vessels, and offshore wind farm support vessels. Each type requires specific crew profiles which we verify before any placement.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you provide DP-certified officers?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency provides Dynamic Positioning Officers and DP-experienced marine crew depending on vessel requirements, certification level, availability, and client specifications. DP certification is verified as part of our standard screening process.\" },\n  { q:\"Do offshore crew need BOSIET certification?\", a:\"BOSIET is required for many offshore roles depending on the project, client, country of operation, transfer method, and offshore installation requirements. We check BOSIET certification validity as part of offshore crew qualification review and can advise based on specific project needs.\" },\n  { q:\"What is HUET training?\", a:\"HUET stands for Helicopter Underwater Escape Training. It is typically required for personnel travelling offshore by helicopter to installations, rigs, or vessels. It covers offshore transfer safety and emergency preparedness for underwater escape situations.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you supply offshore technical personnel?\", a:\"Yes. We supply riggers, welders, scaffolders, ROV technicians, surveyors, HSE officers, safety supervisors, mechanical technicians, electrical technicians, and maintenance crew for offshore vessels, rigs, and project operations.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you provide emergency offshore crew?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency provides urgent offshore crew replacement for sudden unavailability, failed medicals, travel delays, visa issues, project extensions, illness, or sudden workforce gaps. We maintain a pre-screened database specifically for fast offshore deployment.\" },\n  { q:\"How fast can offshore crew be mobilized?\", a:\"Mobilization time depends on the role, certification requirements, offshore medical validity, travel and visa processing, client approval requirements, and offshore project location. Emergency mobilization for pre-certified, medically valid personnel with no travel barriers can happen within 24 to 72 hours depending on the role and destination.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you check offshore medical certification?\", a:\"Yes. Offshore medical certification and fitness for duty are reviewed for all crew and technical personnel according to project, client, and offshore installation requirements. We do not deploy personnel without confirmed medical validity.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you provide offshore crew rotation support?\", a:\"Yes. We support planned crew rotation, relief crew preparation, contract completion, fatigue management planning, and long-term offshore workforce continuity for operators managing ongoing offshore campaigns.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you support oil and gas crew manning?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency provides crew manning for offshore oil and gas marine operations including OSV operations, drilling support, FPSO marine activities, production support, offshore logistics, and HSE-critical offshore roles.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you support offshore wind projects?\", a:\"Yes. We provide marine crew, technical personnel, and offshore logistics support for offshore wind farm support vessels, crew transfer vessels, maintenance operations, and renewable energy offshore logistics.\" },\n  { q:\"How do you verify offshore crew quality?\", a:\"Our verification process covers certification checks, offshore work history review, vessel-type experience evaluation, technical skill assessment, reference checks, HSE awareness review, offshore medical fitness confirmation, and offshore readiness assessment.\" },\n  { q:\"What certifications are commonly required for offshore crew?\", a:\"Commonly required certifications include STCW, OPITO, BOSIET, HUET, DP certification for relevant roles, offshore medical certificates, flag-state documents, certificates of competency, role-specific technical certificates, and client-specific HSE induction requirements.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you supply crew for AHTS and PSV vessels?\", a:\"Yes. We provide crew for anchor handling tug supply vessels and platform supply vessels, covering all deck, marine, engineering, and technical roles. AHTS and PSV crew are screened for offshore deck operations, anchor handling awareness, cargo safety, and offshore vessel experience.\" },\n  { q:\"Can you provide long-term offshore workforce solutions?\", a:\"Yes. ShipCrewAgency supports long-term offshore crew management including rotation planning, compliance documentation tracking, relief crew readiness, retention planning, and ongoing offshore workforce continuity for multi-vessel operators and long-duration campaigns.\" },\n  { q:\"What affects offshore crew manning cost?\", a:\"Cost is affected by role type, technical skill level, project duration, vessel type, certification requirements, travel and visa logistics, urgency level, rotation cycle length, client-specific requirements, and offshore location. Contact our team for a transparent project-specific proposal.\" },\n  { q:\"Do you support international offshore deployment?\", a:\"Yes. We support global offshore deployment including international recruitment, multi-country travel coordination, visa processing support, mobilization planning, and offshore project joining logistics for operations worldwide.\" },\n  { q:\"How can we request offshore crew support?\", a:\"Contact ShipCrewAgency with your project type, vessel type, required positions, certification requirements, mobilization date, offshore location, rotation schedule, and urgency level. Our offshore manning team will review your requirements and respond with a tailored crew supply proposal.\" }\n];\n\nfunction buildFAQs() {\n  const list = document.getElementById('faqList');\n  faqs.forEach(f => {\n    const item = document.createElement('div');\n    item.className = 'faq-item';\n    item.innerHTML = `\n      <button class=\"faq-btn\" onclick=\"toggleFAQ(this)\" aria-expanded=\"false\">\n        <span>${f.q}</span>\n        <svg class=\"faq-ico\" fill=\"none\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\">\n          <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2.5\" d=\"M12 6v6m0 0v6m0-6h6m-6 0H6\"/>\n        </svg>\n      </button>\n      <div class=\"faq-body\">\n        <p class=\"faq-ans\">${f.a}</p>\n      </div>`;\n    list.appendChild(item);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction toggleFAQ(btn) {\n  const body = btn.nextElementSibling;\n  const isOpen = body.classList.contains('open');\n  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-body.open').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('open'));\n  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-btn.open').forEach(b => { b.classList.remove('open'); b.setAttribute('aria-expanded','false'); });\n  if (!isOpen) {\n    body.classList.add('open');\n    btn.classList.add('open');\n    btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded','true');\n  }\n}\n\nfunction submitForm() {\n  document.getElementById('recruitmentForm').style.display = 'none';\n  document.getElementById('formSuccess').style.display = 'block';\n}\n\nbuildFAQs();",
